Preheat your #oven{} to 210°C. Pop the @sweet potato fries{250%g} on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @olive oil{5%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, toss to coat. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until cooked, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{210%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry the chicken until golden brown on each side and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn the chicken every few minutes.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1} then separate the leaves. Thinly slice 1 leaf per person (this is to go in the bun later on). Halve the @brioche hot dog buns{2} down the middle (but not the whole way through).

Meanwhile, put the @mayonnaise{1} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} in a #bowl{}, add the @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp} and @water{50%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together vigorously with a #fork{} until combined. Add the whole baby gem leaves to the bowl, but don't toss together, we'll do that later.

Once the chicken is cooked, reduce the heat to medium. Add the @BBQ sauce{64%g} and @cider vinegar{15%ml} to the frying pan along with the @water{1%tbsp}. Stir everything together, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Simmer until the mixture is thick, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat. Meanwhile, pop the buns in the oven to warm for ~{2%minutes}. Once cooked, taste the sauce and add more salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Pop the sliced baby gem lettuce into the bottom of the buns. Spoon the chicken on top and finish with the remaining hard cheese. Toss the baby gem salad with the dressing and serve on the side along with the fries. Enjoy!